{
  "video_id": "YyXRYgjQXX0",
  "title": "Are you a giver or a taker? | Adam Grant",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12837.0,
      "end_time": 15128.0,
      "text": "I want you to look around the room for a minute"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 15128.0,
      "end_time": 17871.0,
      "text": "and try to find the most paranoid person here --"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 17871.0,
      "end_time": 18959.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 18959.0,
      "end_time": 21435.0,
      "text": "And then I want you to point at that person for me."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 21435.0,
      "end_time": 22494.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 22494.0,
      "end_time": 23877.0,
      "text": "OK, don't actually do it."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 23877.0,
      "end_time": 25020.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 25020.0,
      "end_time": 26913.0,
      "text": "But, as an organizational psychologist,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 26913.0,
      "end_time": 28819.0,
      "text": "I spend a lot of time in workplaces,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 28819.0,
      "end_time": 31532.0,
      "text": "and I find paranoia everywhere."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 31532.0,
      "end_time": 33965.0,
      "text": "Paranoia is caused by people that I call \"takers.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 33965.0,
      "end_time": 36172.0,
      "text": "Takers are self-serving in their interactions."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 36172.0,
      "end_time": 38832.0,
      "text": "It's all about what can you do for me."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 38832.0,
      "end_time": 40257.0,
      "text": "The opposite is a giver."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 40257.0,
      "end_time": 43041.0,
      "text": "It's somebody who approaches most interactions by asking,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 43041.0,
      "end_time": 45165.0,
      "text": "\"What can I do for you?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 45165.0,
      "end_time": 48060.0,
      "text": "I wanted to give you a chance to think about your own style."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 48060.0,
      "end_time": 50037.0,
      "text": "We all have moments of giving and taking."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 50037.0,
      "end_time": 53077.0,
      "text": "Your style is how you treat most of the people most of the time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 53077.0,
      "end_time": 54259.0,
      "text": "your default."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 54259.0,
      "end_time": 55825.0,
      "text": "I have a short test you can take"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 55825.0,
      "end_time": 58348.0,
      "text": "to figure out if you're more of a giver or a taker,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 58348.0,
      "end_time": 59850.0,
      "text": "and you can take it right now."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 59850.0,
      "end_time": 61313.0,
      "text": "[The Narcissist Test]"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 61313.0,
      "end_time": 63649.0,
      "text": "[Step 1: Take a moment to think about yourself.]"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 63649.0,
      "end_time": 64776.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 64775.99999999999,
      "end_time": 67658.0,
      "text": "[Step 2: If you made it to Step 2, you are not a narcissist.]"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 67658.0,
      "end_time": 70082.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 70082.0,
      "end_time": 73939.0,
      "text": "This is the only thing I will say today that has no data behind it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 73939.0,
      "end_time": 77395.0,
      "text": "but I am convinced the longer it takes for you to laugh at this cartoon,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 77395.0,
      "end_time": 79846.0,
      "text": "the more worried we should be that you're a taker."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 79846.0,
      "end_time": 80935.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 80935.0,
      "end_time": 82991.0,
      "text": "Of course, not all takers are narcissists."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 82991.0,
      "end_time": 85903.0,
      "text": "Some are just givers who got burned one too many times."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 85903.0,
      "end_time": 89251.0,
      "text": "Then there's another kind of taker that we won't be addressing today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 89251.0,
      "end_time": 91128.0,
      "text": "and that's called a psychopath."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 91128.0,
      "end_time": 92303.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 92303.0,
      "end_time": 95199.0,
      "text": "I was curious, though, about how common these extremes are,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 95199.0,
      "end_time": 98032.0,
      "text": "and so I surveyed over 30,000 people across industries"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 98032.0,
      "end_time": 99668.0,
      "text": "around the world's cultures."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 99668.0,
      "end_time": 102170.0,
      "text": "And I found that most people are right in the middle"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 102170.0,
      "end_time": 103660.0,
      "text": "between giving and taking."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 103660.0,
      "end_time": 106029.0,
      "text": "They choose this third style called \"matching.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 106029.0,
      "end_time": 109398.0,
      "text": "If you're a matcher, you try to keep an even balance of give and take:"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 109398.0,
      "end_time": 112740.0,
      "text": "quid pro quo -- I'll do something for you if you do something for me."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 112740.0,
      "end_time": 115145.0,
      "text": "And that seems like a safe way to live your life."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 115145.0,
      "end_time": 118353.0,
      "text": "But is it the most effective and productive way to live your life?"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 118353.0,
      "end_time": 120841.0,
      "text": "The answer to that question is a very definitive ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 120841.0,
      "end_time": 122023.0,
      "text": "maybe."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 122023.0,
      "end_time": 123273.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 123273.0,
      "end_time": 125476.0,
      "text": "I studied dozens of organizations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 125476.0,
      "end_time": 126675.0,
      "text": "thousands of people."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 126675.0,
      "end_time": 130251.0,
      "text": "I had engineers measuring their productivity."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 130251.0,
      "end_time": 132630.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 132630.0,
      "end_time": 135623.0,
      "text": "I looked at medical students' grades --"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 135623.0,
      "end_time": 137622.0,
      "text": "even salespeople's revenue."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 137622.0,
      "end_time": 139092.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 139092.0,
      "end_time": 140768.0,
      "text": "And, unexpectedly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 140768.0,
      "end_time": 144749.0,
      "text": "the worst performers in each of these jobs were the givers."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 144749.0,
      "end_time": 146817.0,
      "text": "The engineers who got the least work done"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 146817.0,
      "end_time": 149347.0,
      "text": "were the ones who did more favors than they got back."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 149347.0,
      "end_time": 151507.0,
      "text": "They were so busy doing other people's jobs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 151507.0,
      "end_time": 155081.0,
      "text": "they literally ran out of time and energy to get their own work completed."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 155081.0,
      "end_time": 157910.0,
      "text": "In medical school, the lowest grades belong to the students"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 157910.0,
      "end_time": 160041.0,
      "text": "who agree most strongly with statements like,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 160041.0,
      "end_time": 163068.0,
      "text": "\"I love helping others,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 163068.0,
      "end_time": 165316.0,
      "text": "which suggests the doctor you ought to trust"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 165316.0,
      "end_time": 168419.0,
      "text": "is the one who came to med school with no desire to help anybody."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 168419.0,
      "end_time": 169470.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 169470.0,
      "end_time": 171852.0,
      "text": "And then in sales, too, the lowest revenue accrued"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 171852.0,
      "end_time": 173571.0,
      "text": "in the most generous salespeople."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 173571.0,
      "end_time": 176025.0,
      "text": "I actually reached out to one of those salespeople"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 176025.0,
      "end_time": 177656.0,
      "text": "who had a very high giver score."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 177656.0,
      "end_time": 180238.0,
      "text": "And I asked him, \"Why do you suck at your job --\""
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 180238.0,
      "end_time": 181803.0,
      "text": "I didn't ask it that way, but --"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 181803.0,
      "end_time": 182871.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 182871.0,
      "end_time": 185247.0,
      "text": "\"What's the cost of generosity in sales?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 185247.0,
      "end_time": 188537.0,
      "text": "And he said, \"Well, I just care so deeply about my customers"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 188537.0,
      "end_time": 191323.0,
      "text": "that I would never sell them one of our crappy products.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 191323.0,
      "end_time": 192748.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 192748.0,
      "end_time": 194000.0,
      "text": "So just out of curiosity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 194000.0,
      "end_time": 197308.0,
      "text": "how many of you self-identify more as givers than takers or matchers?"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 197308.0,
      "end_time": 198962.0,
      "text": "Raise your hands."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 198962.0,
      "end_time": 202525.0,
      "text": "OK, it would have been more before we talked about these data."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 202525.0,
      "end_time": 206176.0,
      "text": "But actually, it turns out there's a twist here,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 206176.0,
      "end_time": 209496.0,
      "text": "because givers are often sacrificing themselves,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 209496.0,
      "end_time": 212345.0,
      "text": "but they make their organizations better."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 212345.0,
      "end_time": 215136.0,
      "text": "We have a huge body of evidence --"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 215136.0,
      "end_time": 218893.0,
      "text": "many, many studies looking at the frequency of giving behavior"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 218893.0,
      "end_time": 221054.0,
      "text": "that exists in a team or an organization --"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 221054.0,
      "end_time": 224164.0,
      "text": "and the more often people are helping and sharing their knowledge"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 224164.0,
      "end_time": 225341.0,
      "text": "and providing mentoring,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 225341.0,
      "end_time": 228142.0,
      "text": "the better organizations do on every metric we can measure:"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 228142.0,
      "end_time": 230997.0,
      "text": "higher profits, customer satisfaction, employee retention --"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 230997.0,
      "end_time": 233407.0,
      "text": "even lower operating expenses."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 233407.0,
      "end_time": 236299.0,
      "text": "So givers spend a lot of time trying to help other people"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 236299.0,
      "end_time": 237530.0,
      "text": "and improve the team,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 237530.0,
      "end_time": 240030.0,
      "text": "and then, unfortunately, they suffer along the way."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 240030.0,
      "end_time": 241722.0,
      "text": "I want to talk about what it takes"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 241722.0,
      "end_time": 245564.0,
      "text": "to build cultures where givers actually get to succeed."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 245564.0,
      "end_time": 248608.0,
      "text": "So I wondered, then, if givers are the worst performers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 248608.0,
      "end_time": 251438.0,
      "text": "who are the best performers?"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 251438.0,
      "end_time": 254112.0,
      "text": "Let me start with the good news: it's not the takers."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 254112.0,
      "end_time": 257791.0,
      "text": "Takers tend to rise quickly but also fall quickly in most jobs."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 257791.0,
      "end_time": 259912.0,
      "text": "And they fall at the hands of matchers."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 259911.99999999997,
      "end_time": 263356.0,
      "text": "If you're a matcher, you believe in \"An eye for an eye\" -- a just world."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 263356.0,
      "end_time": 264800.0,
      "text": "And so when you meet a taker,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 264800.0,
      "end_time": 266693.0,
      "text": "you feel like it's your mission in life"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 266693.0,
      "end_time": 268759.0,
      "text": "to just punish the hell out of that person."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 268759.0,
      "end_time": 269797.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 269797.0,
      "end_time": 272108.0,
      "text": "And that way justice gets served."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 272108.0,
      "end_time": 274102.0,
      "text": "Well, most people are matchers."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 274102.0,
      "end_time": 275710.0,
      "text": "And that means if you're a taker,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 275710.0,
      "end_time": 277714.0,
      "text": "it tends to catch up with you eventually;"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 277714.0,
      "end_time": 279376.0,
      "text": "what goes around will come around."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 279376.0,
      "end_time": 281006.0,
      "text": "And so the logical conclusion is:"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 281006.0,
      "end_time": 283895.0,
      "text": "it must be the matchers who are the best performers."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 283895.0,
      "end_time": 285437.0,
      "text": "But they're not."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 285437.0,
      "end_time": 288311.0,
      "text": "In every job, in every organization I've ever studied,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 288311.0,
      "end_time": 291651.0,
      "text": "the best results belong to the givers again."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 291651.0,
      "end_time": 294833.0,
      "text": "Take a look at some data I gathered from hundreds of salespeople,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 294833.0,
      "end_time": 296010.0,
      "text": "tracking their revenue."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 296010.0,
      "end_time": 298689.0,
      "text": "What you can see is that the givers go to both extremes."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 298689.0,
      "end_time": 301931.0,
      "text": "They make up the majority of people who bring in the lowest revenue,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 301931.0,
      "end_time": 303421.0,
      "text": "but also the highest revenue."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 303421.0,
      "end_time": 306049.0,
      "text": "The same patterns were true for engineers' productivity"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 306049.0,
      "end_time": 307464.0,
      "text": "and medical students' grades."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 307464.0,
      "end_time": 310095.0,
      "text": "Givers are overrepresented at the bottom and at the top"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 310095.0,
      "end_time": 312201.0,
      "text": "of every success metric that I can track."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 312201.0,
      "end_time": 313527.0,
      "text": "Which raises the question:"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 313527.0,
      "end_time": 316960.0,
      "text": "How do we create a world where more of these givers get to excel?"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 316960.0,
      "end_time": 319807.0,
      "text": "I want to talk about how to do that, not just in businesses,"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 319807.0,
      "end_time": 321662.0,
      "text": "but also in nonprofits, schools --"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 321662.0,
      "end_time": 322979.0,
      "text": "even governments."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 322979.0,
      "end_time": 324209.0,
      "text": "Are you ready?"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 324209.0,
      "end_time": 325419.0,
      "text": "(Cheers)"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 325419.0,
      "end_time": 328435.0,
      "text": "I was going to do it anyway, but I appreciate the enthusiasm."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 328435.0,
      "end_time": 329482.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 329482.0,
      "end_time": 331350.0,
      "text": "The first thing that's really critical"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 331350.0,
      "end_time": 334121.0,
      "text": "is to recognize that givers are your most valuable people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 334121.0,
      "end_time": 336579.0,
      "text": "but if they're not careful, they burn out."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 336579.0,
      "end_time": 339093.0,
      "text": "So you have to protect the givers in your midst."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 339093.0,
      "end_time": 344993.0,
      "text": "And I learned a great lesson about this from Fortune's best networker."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 344993.0,
      "end_time": 346367.0,
      "text": "It's the guy, not the cat."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 346367.0,
      "end_time": 347551.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 347551.0,
      "end_time": 349331.0,
      "text": "His name is Adam Rifkin."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 349331.0,
      "end_time": 351567.0,
      "text": "He's a very successful serial entrepreneur"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 351567.0,
      "end_time": 354385.0,
      "text": "who spends a huge amount of his time helping other people."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 354385.0,
      "end_time": 357261.0,
      "text": "And his secret weapon is the five-minute favor."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 357261.0,
      "end_time": 359944.0,
      "text": "Adam said, \"You don't have to be Mother Teresa or Gandhi"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 359944.0,
      "end_time": 361151.0,
      "text": "to be a giver."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 361151.0,
      "end_time": 363678.0,
      "text": "You just have to find small ways to add large value"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 363678.0,
      "end_time": 365059.0,
      "text": "to other people's lives.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 365059.0,
      "end_time": 367426.0,
      "text": "That could be as simple as making an introduction"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 367426.0,
      "end_time": 370381.0,
      "text": "between two people who could benefit from knowing each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 370381.0,
      "end_time": 373742.0,
      "text": "It could be sharing your knowledge or giving a little bit of feedback."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 373742.0,
      "end_time": 376078.0,
      "text": "Or It might be even something as basic as saying,"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 376078.0,
      "end_time": 377331.0,
      "text": "\"You know,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 377331.0,
      "end_time": 378855.0,
      "text": "I'm going to try and figure out"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 378855.0,
      "end_time": 382462.0,
      "text": "if I can recognize somebody whose work has gone unnoticed.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 382462.0,
      "end_time": 384780.0,
      "text": "And those five-minute favors are really critical"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 384780.0,
      "end_time": 387962.0,
      "text": "to helping givers set boundaries and protect themselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 387962.0,
      "end_time": 389431.0,
      "text": "The second thing that matters"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 389431.0,
      "end_time": 391923.0,
      "text": "if you want to build a culture where givers succeed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 391923.0,
      "end_time": 394872.0,
      "text": "is you actually need a culture where help-seeking is the norm;"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 394872.0,
      "end_time": 396536.0,
      "text": "where people ask a lot."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 396536.0,
      "end_time": 399229.0,
      "text": "This may hit a little too close to home for some of you."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 399229.0,
      "end_time": 402292.0,
      "text": "[So in all your relationships, you always have to be the giver?]"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 402292.0,
      "end_time": 403340.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 403340.0,
      "end_time": 405095.0,
      "text": "What you see with successful givers"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 405095.0,
      "end_time": 408754.0,
      "text": "is they recognize that it's OK to be a receiver, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 408754.0,
      "end_time": 411641.0,
      "text": "If you run an organization, we can actually make this easier."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 411641.0,
      "end_time": 413962.0,
      "text": "We can make it easier for people to ask for help."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 413962.0,
      "end_time": 416058.0,
      "text": "A couple colleagues and I studied hospitals."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 416058.0,
      "end_time": 419284.0,
      "text": "We found that on certain floors, nurses did a lot of help-seeking,"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 419284.0,
      "end_time": 421559.0,
      "text": "and on other floors, they did very little of it."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 421559.0,
      "end_time": 424929.0,
      "text": "The factor that stood out on the floors where help-seeking was common,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 424929.0,
      "end_time": 426104.0,
      "text": "where it was the norm,"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 426104.0,
      "end_time": 428503.0,
      "text": "was there was just one nurse whose sole job it was"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 428503.0,
      "end_time": 430558.0,
      "text": "to help other nurses on the unit."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 430558.0,
      "end_time": 431963.0,
      "text": "When that role was available,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 431963.0,
      "end_time": 435644.0,
      "text": "nurses said, \"It's not embarrassing, it's not vulnerable to ask for help --"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 435644.0,
      "end_time": 438263.0,
      "text": "it's actually encouraged.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 438263.0,
      "end_time": 441113.0,
      "text": "Help-seeking isn't important just for protecting the success"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 441113.0,
      "end_time": 442536.0,
      "text": "and the well-being of givers."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 442536.0,
      "end_time": 445492.0,
      "text": "It's also critical to getting more people to act like givers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 445492.0,
      "end_time": 446705.0,
      "text": "because the data say"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 446705.0,
      "end_time": 450129.0,
      "text": "that somewhere between 75 and 90 percent of all giving in organizations"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 450129.0,
      "end_time": 451996.0,
      "text": "starts with a request."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 451996.0,
      "end_time": 453468.0,
      "text": "But a lot of people don't ask."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 453468.0,
      "end_time": 455240.0,
      "text": "They don't want to look incompetent,"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 455240.0,
      "end_time": 458291.0,
      "text": "they don't know where to turn, they don't want to burden others."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 458291.0,
      "end_time": 460024.0,
      "text": "Yet if nobody ever asks for help,"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 460024.0,
      "end_time": 462723.0,
      "text": "you have a lot of frustrated givers in your organization"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 462723.0,
      "end_time": 464730.0,
      "text": "who would love to step up and contribute,"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 464730.0,
      "end_time": 467413.0,
      "text": "if they only knew who could benefit and how."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 467413.0,
      "end_time": 469235.0,
      "text": "But I think the most important thing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 469235.0,
      "end_time": 471735.0,
      "text": "if you want to build a culture of successful givers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 471735.0,
      "end_time": 474561.0,
      "text": "is to be thoughtful about who you let onto your team."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 474561.0,
      "end_time": 477601.0,
      "text": "I figured, you want a culture of productive generosity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 477601.0,
      "end_time": 479597.0,
      "text": "you should hire a bunch of givers."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 479597.0,
      "end_time": 483715.0,
      "text": "But I was surprised to discover, actually, that that was not right --"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 483715.0,
      "end_time": 486214.0,
      "text": "that the negative impact of a taker on a culture"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 486214.0,
      "end_time": 489530.0,
      "text": "is usually double to triple the positive impact of a giver."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 489530.0,
      "end_time": 490704.0,
      "text": "Think about it this way:"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 490704.0,
      "end_time": 492392.0,
      "text": "one bad apple can spoil a barrel,"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 492392.0,
      "end_time": 495942.0,
      "text": "but one good egg just does not make a dozen."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 495942.0,
      "end_time": 497518.0,
      "text": "I don't know what that means --"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 497518.0,
      "end_time": 498661.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 498661.0,
      "end_time": 500058.0,
      "text": "But I hope you do."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 500058.0,
      "end_time": 503404.0,
      "text": "No -- let even one taker into a team,"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 503404.0,
      "end_time": 506648.0,
      "text": "and you will see that the givers will stop helping."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 506648.0,
      "end_time": 509602.0,
      "text": "They'll say, \"I'm surrounded by a bunch of snakes and sharks."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 509602.0,
      "end_time": 510992.0,
      "text": "Why should I contribute?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 510992.0,
      "end_time": 512992.0,
      "text": "Whereas if you let one giver into a team,"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 512991.99999999994,
      "end_time": 515137.99999999994,
      "text": "you don't get an explosion of generosity."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 515138.00000000006,
      "end_time": 516583.00000000006,
      "text": "More often, people are like,"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 516582.99999999994,
      "end_time": 519076.99999999994,
      "text": "\"Great! That person can do all our work.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 519077.0,
      "end_time": 521847.0,
      "text": "So, effective hiring and screening and team building"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 521847.0,
      "end_time": 524007.0,
      "text": "is not about bringing in the givers;"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 524006.99999999994,
      "end_time": 527036.0,
      "text": "it's about weeding out the takers."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 527036.0,
      "end_time": 528211.0,
      "text": "If you can do that well,"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 528211.0,
      "end_time": 530177.0,
      "text": "you'll be left with givers and matchers."
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 530177.0,
      "end_time": 531566.0,
      "text": "The givers will be generous"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 531566.0,
      "end_time": 534224.0,
      "text": "because they don't have to worry about the consequences."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 534224.0,
      "end_time": 537361.0,
      "text": "And the beauty of the matchers is that they follow the norm."
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 537361.0,
      "end_time": 540745.0,
      "text": "So how do you catch a taker before it's too late?"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 540745.0,
      "end_time": 543656.0,
      "text": "We're actually pretty bad at figuring out who's a taker,"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 543656.0,
      "end_time": 545506.0,
      "text": "especially on first impressions."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 545506.0,
      "end_time": 547838.0,
      "text": "There's a personality trait that throws us off."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 547838.0,
      "end_time": 549167.0,
      "text": "It's called agreeableness,"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 549167.0,
      "end_time": 551812.0,
      "text": "one the major dimensions of personality across cultures."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 551812.0,
      "end_time": 555321.0,
      "text": "Agreeable people are warm and friendly, they're nice, they're polite."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 555321.0,
      "end_time": 557136.0,
      "text": "You find a lot of them in Canada --"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 557136.0,
      "end_time": 558763.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 558763.0,
      "end_time": 562284.0,
      "text": "Where there was actually a national contest"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 562284.0,
      "end_time": 565338.0,
      "text": "to come up with a new Canadian slogan and fill in the blank,"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 565338.0,
      "end_time": 566937.0,
      "text": "\"As Canadian as ...\""
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 566937.0,
      "end_time": 569045.0,
      "text": "I thought the winning entry was going to be,"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 569045.0,
      "end_time": 571540.0,
      "text": "\"As Canadian as maple syrup,\" or, \"... ice hockey.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 571540.0,
      "end_time": 574549.0,
      "text": "But no, Canadians voted for their new national slogan to be --"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 574549.0,
      "end_time": 575734.0,
      "text": "I kid you not --"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 575734.0,
      "end_time": 578189.0,
      "text": "\"As Canadian as possible under the circumstances.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 578189.0,
      "end_time": 582020.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 582020.0,
      "end_time": 584415.0,
      "text": "Now for those of you who are highly agreeable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 584415.0,
      "end_time": 585832.0,
      "text": "or maybe slightly Canadian,"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 585832.0,
      "end_time": 587229.0,
      "text": "you get this right away."
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 587229.0,
      "end_time": 589070.0,
      "text": "How could I ever say I'm any one thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 589070.0,
      "end_time": 592400.0,
      "text": "when I'm constantly adapting to try to please other people?"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 592400.0,
      "end_time": 594247.0,
      "text": "Disagreeable people do less of it."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 594247.0,
      "end_time": 597208.0,
      "text": "They're more critical, skeptical, challenging,"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 597208.0,
      "end_time": 600286.0,
      "text": "and far more likely than their peers to go to law school."
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 600286.0,
      "end_time": 601453.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 601453.0,
      "end_time": 604132.0,
      "text": "That's not a joke, that's actually an empirical fact."
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 604132.0,
      "end_time": 605215.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 605215.0,
      "end_time": 607788.0,
      "text": "So I always assumed that agreeable people were givers"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 607788.0,
      "end_time": 609759.0,
      "text": "and disagreeable people were takers."
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 609759.0,
      "end_time": 611213.0,
      "text": "But then I gathered the data,"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 611213.0,
      "end_time": 614350.0,
      "text": "and I was stunned to find no correlation between those traits,"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 614350.0,
      "end_time": 617033.0,
      "text": "because it turns out that agreeableness-disagreeableness"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 617033.0,
      "end_time": 618220.0,
      "text": "is your outer veneer:"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 618220.0,
      "end_time": 620185.0,
      "text": "How pleasant is it to interact with you?"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 620185.0,
      "end_time": 622901.0,
      "text": "Whereas giving and taking are more of your inner motives:"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 622901.0,
      "end_time": 625817.0,
      "text": "What are your values? What are your intentions toward others?"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 625817.0,
      "end_time": 628033.0,
      "text": "If you really want to judge people accurately,"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 628033.0,
      "end_time": 631574.0,
      "text": "you have to get to the moment every consultant in the room is waiting for,"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 631574.0,
      "end_time": 632763.0,
      "text": "and draw a two-by-two."
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 632763.0,
      "end_time": 637648.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 637648.0,
      "end_time": 639679.0,
      "text": "The agreeable givers are easy to spot:"
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 639679.0,
      "end_time": 643740.0,
      "text": "they say yes to everything."
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 643740.0,
      "end_time": 646637.0,
      "text": "The disagreeable takers are also recognized quickly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 646637.0,
      "end_time": 650568.0,
      "text": "although you might call them by a slightly different name."
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 650568.0,
      "end_time": 653828.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 653828.0,
      "end_time": 655924.0,
      "text": "We forget about the other two combinations."
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 655924.0,
      "end_time": 659283.0,
      "text": "There are disagreeable givers in our organizations."
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 659283.0,
      "end_time": 661948.0,
      "text": "There are people who are gruff and tough on the surface"
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 661948.0,
      "end_time": 665089.0,
      "text": "but underneath have others' best interests at heart."
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 665089.0,
      "end_time": 666476.0,
      "text": "Or as an engineer put it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 666476.0,
      "end_time": 668106.0,
      "text": "\"Oh, disagreeable givers --"
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 668106.0,
      "end_time": 672006.0,
      "text": "like somebody with a bad user interface but a great operating system.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 672006.0,
      "end_time": 673316.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 673316.0,
      "end_time": 674711.0,
      "text": "If that helps you."
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 674711.0,
      "end_time": 676424.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 676424.0,
      "end_time": 679951.0,
      "text": "Disagreeable givers are the most undervalued people in our organizations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 679951.0,
      "end_time": 682567.0,
      "text": "because they're the ones who give the critical feedback"
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 682567.0,
      "end_time": 685197.0,
      "text": "that no one wants to hear but everyone needs to hear."
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 685197.0,
      "end_time": 687709.0,
      "text": "We need to do a much better job valuing these people"
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 687709.0,
      "end_time": 689521.0,
      "text": "as opposed to writing them off early,"
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 689521.0,
      "end_time": 691289.0,
      "text": "and saying, \"Eh, kind of prickly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 691289.0,
      "end_time": 693849.0,
      "text": "must be a selfish taker.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 693849.0,
      "end_time": 696632.0,
      "text": "The other combination we forget about is the deadly one --"
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 696632.0,
      "end_time": 700444.0,
      "text": "the agreeable taker, also known as the faker."
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 700444.0,
      "end_time": 702533.0,
      "text": "This is the person who's nice to your face,"
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 702533.0,
      "end_time": 704537.0,
      "text": "and then will stab you right in the back."
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 704537.0,
      "end_time": 706537.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 706537.0,
      "end_time": 709795.0,
      "text": "And my favorite way to catch these people in the interview process"
    },
    {
      "index": 297,
      "start_time": 709795.0,
      "end_time": 711091.0,
      "text": "is to ask the question,"
    },
    {
      "index": 298,
      "start_time": 711091.0,
      "end_time": 713077.0,
      "text": "\"Can you give me the names of four people"
    },
    {
      "index": 299,
      "start_time": 713077.0,
      "end_time": 716424.0,
      "text": "whose careers you have fundamentally improved?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 300,
      "start_time": 716424.0,
      "end_time": 718341.0,
      "text": "The takers will give you four names,"
    },
    {
      "index": 301,
      "start_time": 718341.0,
      "end_time": 721062.0,
      "text": "and they will all be more influential than them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 302,
      "start_time": 721062.0,
      "end_time": 724957.0,
      "text": "because takers are great at kissing up and then kicking down."
    },
    {
      "index": 303,
      "start_time": 724957.0,
      "end_time": 728381.0,
      "text": "Givers are more likely to name people who are below them in a hierarchy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 304,
      "start_time": 728381.0,
      "end_time": 729951.0,
      "text": "who don't have as much power,"
    },
    {
      "index": 305,
      "start_time": 729951.0,
      "end_time": 731723.0,
      "text": "who can do them no good."
    },
    {
      "index": 306,
      "start_time": 731723.0,
      "end_time": 734921.0,
      "text": "And let's face it, you all know you can learn a lot about character"
    },
    {
      "index": 307,
      "start_time": 734921.0,
      "end_time": 737500.0,
      "text": "by watching how someone treats their restaurant server"
    },
    {
      "index": 308,
      "start_time": 737500.0,
      "end_time": 739319.0,
      "text": "or their Uber driver."
    },
    {
      "index": 309,
      "start_time": 739319.0,
      "end_time": 740609.0,
      "text": "So if we do all this well,"
    },
    {
      "index": 310,
      "start_time": 740609.0,
      "end_time": 742717.0,
      "text": "if we can weed takers out of organizations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 311,
      "start_time": 742717.0,
      "end_time": 744653.0,
      "text": "if we can make it safe to ask for help,"
    },
    {
      "index": 312,
      "start_time": 744653.0,
      "end_time": 746691.0,
      "text": "if we can protect givers from burnout"
    },
    {
      "index": 313,
      "start_time": 746691.0,
      "end_time": 749942.0,
      "text": "and make it OK for them to be ambitious in pursuing their own goals"
    },
    {
      "index": 314,
      "start_time": 749942.0,
      "end_time": 752122.0,
      "text": "as well as trying to help other people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 315,
      "start_time": 752122.0,
      "end_time": 755053.0,
      "text": "we can actually change the way that people define success."
    },
    {
      "index": 316,
      "start_time": 755053.0,
      "end_time": 758429.0,
      "text": "Instead of saying it's all about winning a competition,"
    },
    {
      "index": 317,
      "start_time": 758429.0,
      "end_time": 762761.0,
      "text": "people will realize success is really more about contribution."
    },
    {
      "index": 318,
      "start_time": 762761.0,
      "end_time": 765146.0,
      "text": "I believe that the most meaningful way to succeed"
    },
    {
      "index": 319,
      "start_time": 765146.0,
      "end_time": 767040.0,
      "text": "is to help other people succeed."
    },
    {
      "index": 320,
      "start_time": 767040.0,
      "end_time": 768735.0,
      "text": "And if we can spread that belief,"
    },
    {
      "index": 321,
      "start_time": 768735.0,
      "end_time": 771410.0,
      "text": "we can actually turn paranoia upside down."
    },
    {
      "index": 322,
      "start_time": 771410.0,
      "end_time": 772597.0,
      "text": "There's a name for that."
    },
    {
      "index": 323,
      "start_time": 772597.0,
      "end_time": 775025.0,
      "text": "It's called \"pronoia.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 324,
      "start_time": 775025.0,
      "end_time": 776746.0,
      "text": "Pronoia is the delusional belief"
    },
    {
      "index": 325,
      "start_time": 776746.0,
      "end_time": 779370.0,
      "text": "that other people are plotting your well-being."
    },
    {
      "index": 326,
      "start_time": 779370.0,
      "end_time": 782908.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 327,
      "start_time": 782908.0,
      "end_time": 785485.0,
      "text": "That they're going around behind your back"
    },
    {
      "index": 328,
      "start_time": 785485.0,
      "end_time": 789647.0,
      "text": "and saying exceptionally glowing things about you."
    },
    {
      "index": 329,
      "start_time": 789647.0,
      "end_time": 793480.0,
      "text": "The great thing about a culture of givers is that's not a delusion --"
    },
    {
      "index": 330,
      "start_time": 793480.0,
      "end_time": 795697.0,
      "text": "it's reality."
    },
    {
      "index": 331,
      "start_time": 795697.0,
      "end_time": 798297.0,
      "text": "I want to live in a world where givers succeed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 332,
      "start_time": 798297.0,
      "end_time": 800643.0,
      "text": "and I hope you will help me create that world."
    },
    {
      "index": 333,
      "start_time": 800643.0,
      "end_time": 801888.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 334,
      "start_time": 801888.0,
      "end_time": 811888.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}